Genitalia (Fig. 
13
): Two short spermathecae separated by heavily sclerotized short area, spermathecal stalk narrower than spermathecal bulb.

Color (
Fig. 14
): Carapace, coxae, labium, sternum and maxila black. Legs with black short setae and long golden setae. Femora, patellae and tibiae with distal pale rings and inconspicuous stripes on patellae. All the body with blue iridescence. Abdomen black with long red setae on dorsal area.

Color pattern (Fig. 
15
): As in female, but without blue iridescence.

Distribution. Brazil , States of Bahia and Minas Gerais, on the "Serra do Espinhaço" range and its disjunctions (from 21 ° 10 ' to 10 ° S) (
Fig. 19
).
